  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Pest/Vector Control Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company:</strong> Repair.sg<br /><strong>Working Days:</strong> 5.5 days per week<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-time<br /><strong>Salary:</strong> $2,000 – $3,000 </p><h3><strong>Job Summary</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a reliable and experienced <strong>Vector Control Technician</strong> to perform onsite pest and vector management services. Candidates <strong>must have a valid NEA Vector Control Technician Licence</strong> and <strong>at least 1 year of relevant experience</strong>. A company vehicle is provided and may be driven home.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Travel to customer locations to carry out vector control and pest treatment services.</p></li><li><p>Conduct inspections, identify pest/vector issues, and determine appropriate treatment methods.</p></li><li><p>Apply chemicals and perform treatments safely in line with NEA guidelines.</p></li><li><p>Communicate clearly with customers about the treatment process and aftercare.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate service reports, job documentation, and records.</p></li><li><p>Ensure equipment, tools, and company vehicle are well-maintained.</p></li><li><p>Follow safety protocols and proper handling of chemicals at all times.</p></li><li><p>Assist with operational tasks and perform ad hoc duties assigned by the supervisor.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements / Qualifications</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Valid NEA Vector Control Technician Licence.</p></li><li><p>Class 3/3A driving licence - company vehicle provided.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1 year of experience in pest or vector control.</p></li><li><p>Comfortable with outdoor, hands-on fieldwork.</p></li><li><p>Responsible, punctual, and able to work independently.</p></li><li><p>Able to communicate professionally with customers.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Company vehicle provided that may be driven home.</p></li><li><p>Opportunities for skill development and upskilling.</p></li><li><p>Supportive team environment.</p></li><li><p>Statutory benefits included.</p></li></ul>",
